      "lesson title": "Edge AI in Production Lines",
      "order": 1,
      "Description": "This lesson introduces the core concepts behind deploying artificial intelligence directly on devices within manufacturing and production environments. You will explore what Edge AI means in practice, how it differs from cloud-based processing, and why it is increasingly being adopted on the factory floor. The lesson covers the key security and reliability challenges that arise when AI runs on local hardware, including risks around data integrity, device vulnerabilities, and system downtime. By the end, you will have a clear foundation for understanding why these challenges matter and how they can affect the safety and efficiency of a production line. No prior experience with AI or manufacturing technology is required, making this an ideal starting point for anyone new to the subject.",
